{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a pediatrician and an anesthesiologist,"},{"time":2000,"text":"so I put children to sleep for a living."},{"time":4000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":6000,"text":"And I'm an academic, so I put audiences to sleep for free."},{"time":9000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":13000,"text":"But what I actually mostly do"},{"time":15000,"text":"is I manage the pain management service"},{"time":17000,"text":"at the Packard Children's Hospital up at Stanford in Palo Alto."},{"time":20000,"text":"And it's from the experience"},{"time":22000,"text":"from about 20 or 25 years of doing that"},{"time":24000,"text":"that I want to bring to you the message this morning,"},{"time":26000,"text":"that pain is a disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"Now most of the time,"},{"time":30000,"text":"you think of pain as a symptom of a disease,"},{"time":32000,"text":"and that's true most of the time."},{"time":34000,"text":"It's the symptom of a tumor or an infection"},{"time":37000,"text":"or an inflammation or an operation."},{"time":39000,"text":"But about 10 percent of the time,"},{"time":42000,"text":"after the patient has recovered from one of those events,"},{"time":45000,"text":"pain persists."},{"time":47000,"text":"It persists for months"},{"time":49000,"text":"and oftentimes for years,"},{"time":51000,"text":"and when that happens,"},{"time":53000,"text":"it is its own disease."},{"time":55000,"text":"And before I tell you about how it is that we think that happens"},{"time":58000,"text":"and what we can do about it,"},{"time":60000,"text":"I want to show you how it feels for my patients."},{"time":63000,"text":"So imagine, if you will,"},{"time":65000,"text":"that I'm stroking your arm with this feather,"},{"time":67000,"text":"as I'm stroking my arm right now."},{"time":70000,"text":"Now, I want you to imagine"},{"time":72000,"text":"that I'm stroking it with this."},{"time":74000,"text":"Please keep your seat."},{"time":76000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":78000,"text":"A very different feeling."},{"time":80000,"text":"Now what does it have to do with chronic pain?"},{"time":82000,"text":"Imagine, if you will, these two ideas together."},{"time":85000,"text":"Imagine what your life would be like"},{"time":87000,"text":"if I were to stroke it with this feather,"},{"time":90000,"text":"but your brain was telling you"},{"time":92000,"text":"that this is what you are feeling --"},{"time":94000,"text":"and that is the experience of my patients with chronic pain."},{"time":97000,"text":"In fact, imagine something even worse."},{"time":99000,"text":"Imagine I were to stroke your child's arm with this feather,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and their brain [was] telling them"},{"time":104000,"text":"that they were feeling this hot torch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107000,"text":"That was the experience of my patient, Chandler,"},{"time":109000,"text":"whom you see in the photograph."},{"time":111000,"text":"As you can see, she's a beautiful, young woman."},{"time":113000,"text":"She was 16 years old last year when I met her,"},{"time":115000,"text":"and she aspired to be a professional dancer."},{"time":118000,"text":"And during the course of one of her dance rehearsals,"},{"time":120000,"text":"she fell on her outstretched arm and sprained her wrist."},{"time":123000,"text":"Now you would probably imagine, as she did,"},{"time":125000,"text":"that a wrist sprain is a trivial event"},{"time":127000,"text":"in a person's life."},{"time":129000,"text":"Wrap it in an ACE bandage,"},{"time":131000,"text":"take some ibuprofen for a week or two,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and that's the end of the story."},{"time":135000,"text":"But in Chandler's case, that was the beginning of the story."},{"time":139000,"text":"This is what her arm looked like"},{"time":141000,"text":"when she came to my clinic about three months after her sprain."},{"time":144000,"text":"You can see that the arm is discolored,"},{"time":146000,"text":"purplish in color."},{"time":148000,"text":"It was cadaverically cold to the touch."},{"time":150000,"text":"The muscles were frozen, paralyzed --"},{"time":152000,"text":"dystonic is how we refer to that."},{"time":155000,"text":"The pain had spread from her wrist to her hands,"},{"time":158000,"text":"to her fingertips, from her wrist up to her elbow,"},{"time":161000,"text":"almost all the way to her shoulder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"But the worst part was,"},{"time":165000,"text":"not the spontaneous pain that was there 24 hours a day."},{"time":168000,"text":"The worst part was that she had allodynia,"},{"time":171000,"text":"the medical term for the phenomenon that I just illustrated"},{"time":174000,"text":"with the feather and with the torch."},{"time":176000,"text":"The lightest touch of her arm --"},{"time":178000,"text":"the touch of a hand,"},{"time":180000,"text":"the touch even of a sleeve, of a garment, as she put it on --"},{"time":183000,"text":"caused excruciating, burning pain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"How can the nervous system get this so wrong?"},{"time":190000,"text":"How can the nervous system"},{"time":192000,"text":"misinterpret an innocent sensation"},{"time":194000,"text":"like the touch of a hand"},{"time":196000,"text":"and turn it into the malevolent sensation"},{"time":199000,"text":"of the touch of the flame?"},{"time":201000,"text":"Well you probably imagine that the nervous system in the body"},{"time":204000,"text":"is hardwired like your house."},{"time":206000,"text":"In your house, wires run in the wall,"},{"time":208000,"text":"from the light switch to a junction box in the ceiling"},{"time":211000,"text":"and from the junction box to the light bulb."},{"time":214000,"text":"And when you turn the switch on, the light goes on."},{"time":216000,"text":"And when you turn the switch off, the light goes off."},{"time":219000,"text":"So people imagine the nervous system is just like that."},{"time":223000,"text":"If you hit your thumb with a hammer,"},{"time":225000,"text":"these wires in your arm -- that, of course, we call nerves --"},{"time":228000,"text":"transmit the information into the junction box in the spinal cord"},{"time":231000,"text":"where new wires, new nerves,"},{"time":233000,"text":"take the information up to the brain"},{"time":235000,"text":"where you become consciously aware that your thumb is now hurt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"But the situation, of course, in the human body"},{"time":241000,"text":"is far more complicated than that."},{"time":244000,"text":"Instead of it being the case"},{"time":246000,"text":"that that junction box in the spinal cord"},{"time":248000,"text":"is just simple where one nerve connects with the next nerve"},{"time":251000,"text":"by releasing these little brown packets"},{"time":253000,"text":"of chemical information called neurotransmitters"},{"time":256000,"text":"in a linear one-on-one fashion,"},{"time":259000,"text":"in fact, what happens"},{"time":261000,"text":"is the neurotransmitters spill out in three dimensions --"},{"time":263000,"text":"laterally, vertically, up and down in the spinal cord --"},{"time":266000,"text":"and they start interacting"},{"time":268000,"text":"with other adjacent cells."},{"time":271000,"text":"These cells, called glial cells,"},{"time":273000,"text":"were once thought to be"},{"time":275000,"text":"unimportant structural elements of the spinal cord"},{"time":277000,"text":"that did nothing more than hold all the important things together,"},{"time":279000,"text":"like the nerves."},{"time":281000,"text":"But it turns out"},{"time":283000,"text":"the glial cells have a vital role"},{"time":285000,"text":"in the modulation, amplification"},{"time":287000,"text":"and, in the case of pain, the distortion"},{"time":290000,"text":"of sensory experiences."},{"time":293000,"text":"These glial cells become activated."},{"time":295000,"text":"Their DNA starts to synthesize new proteins,"},{"time":297000,"text":"which spill out"},{"time":299000,"text":"and interact with adjacent nerves,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and they start releasing their neurotransmitters,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and those neurotransmitters spill out"},{"time":306000,"text":"and activate adjacent glial cells, and so on and so forth,"},{"time":309000,"text":"until what we have"},{"time":311000,"text":"is a positive feedback loop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"It's almost as if somebody came into your home"},{"time":315000,"text":"and rewired your walls"},{"time":317000,"text":"so that the next time you turned on the light switch,"},{"time":319000,"text":"the toilet flushed three doors down,"},{"time":321000,"text":"or your dishwasher went on,"},{"time":323000,"text":"or your computer monitor turned off."},{"time":325000,"text":"That's crazy,"},{"time":327000,"text":"but that's, in fact, what happens"},{"time":329000,"text":"with chronic pain."},{"time":331000,"text":"And that's why pain becomes its own disease."},{"time":334000,"text":"The nervous system has plasticity."},{"time":336000,"text":"It changes, and it morphs"},{"time":338000,"text":"in response to stimuli."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340000,"text":"Well, what do we do about that?"},{"time":342000,"text":"What can we do in a case like Chandler's?"},{"time":345000,"text":"We treat these patients in a rather crude fashion"},{"time":347000,"text":"at this point in time."},{"time":349000,"text":"We treat them with symptom-modifying drugs --"},{"time":352000,"text":"painkillers --"},{"time":354000,"text":"which are, frankly, not very effective"},{"time":356000,"text":"for this kind of pain."},{"time":358000,"text":"We take nerves that are noisy and active"},{"time":360000,"text":"that should be quiet,"},{"time":362000,"text":"and we put them to sleep with local anesthetics."},{"time":364000,"text":"And most importantly, what we do"},{"time":367000,"text":"is we use a rigorous, and often uncomfortable, process"},{"time":371000,"text":"of physical therapy and occupational therapy"},{"time":374000,"text":"to retrain the nerves in the nervous system"},{"time":377000,"text":"to respond normally"},{"time":380000,"text":"to the activities and sensory experiences"},{"time":383000,"text":"that are part of everyday life."},{"time":385000,"text":"And we support all of that"},{"time":387000,"text":"with an intensive psychotherapy program"},{"time":390000,"text":"to address the despondency, despair and depression"},{"time":393000,"text":"that always accompanies"},{"time":395000,"text":"severe, chronic pain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"It's successful,"},{"time":399000,"text":"as you can see from this video of Chandler,"},{"time":401000,"text":"who, two months after we first met her,"},{"time":403000,"text":"is now doings a back flip."},{"time":405000,"text":"And I had lunch with her yesterday"},{"time":407000,"text":"because she's a college student studying dance at Long Beach here,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and she's doing absolutely fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"But the future is actually even brighter."},{"time":416000,"text":"The future holds the promise"},{"time":419000,"text":"that new drugs will be developed"},{"time":421000,"text":"that are not symptom-modifying drugs"},{"time":424000,"text":"that simply mask the problem,"},{"time":426000,"text":"as we have now,"},{"time":428000,"text":"but that will be disease-modifying drugs"},{"time":431000,"text":"that will actually go right to the root of the problem"},{"time":433000,"text":"and attack those glial cells,"},{"time":435000,"text":"or those pernicious proteins"},{"time":437000,"text":"that the glial cells elaborate,"},{"time":440000,"text":"that spill over and cause this central nervous system wind-up,"},{"time":443000,"text":"or plasticity,"},{"time":445000,"text":"that so is capable"},{"time":447000,"text":"of distorting and amplifying"},{"time":449000,"text":"the sensory experience that we call pain."},{"time":451000,"text":"So I have hope"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"that in the future,"},{"time":455000,"text":"the prophetic words of George Carlin will be realized,"},{"time":458000,"text":"who said, \"My philosophy:"},{"time":460000,"text":"No pain, no pain.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}